The paper focuses on improving the annotation of DeepFashion dataset for fine-grained attribute recognition, which is a task related to computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a neural network with pairwise ranking loss function, which falls under machine learning (LG) sub-category. Moreover, the paper involves data cleaning and merging, which can be related to multimedia (MM) and information retrieval (IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses a multi-label classification approach, which is a common technique in natural language processing (CL) sub-category.
